<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/2947: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Boal</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-12T19:00:00-04:00">July 12, 1937—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>138. Your 184, July 10, 5 p.m. The Department is making a study of the
                            points raised in your telegram. Meanwhile your attention is invited to
                            Embassy’s despatch 245 January 11, 1928<note n="50" xml:id="d638fn50">Not printed.</note> and its enclosure, and its despatch 474 March
                            27, 1928<note n="51" xml:id="d638fn51"><ref target="frus1928v03#pg_300"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 300</ref>.</note> and its
                            enclosures.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>